div.p:
Take of the magiſtral water of Earth-worms,
two ounces; Elixir Proprietatis, ſix drops: mix;
and exhibit it twice a day.

Take the Decoction of Sage or of Hyſſop.
Diſſolve it in the Confection of Muſtard-ſeed;
and gargal it in the Mouth and Throat.

Take of the Conſerve of the flowers of Betony,
Tamarisk, and male Peony, of each two ounces;
Species Diamargariton frigidæ, a dram and a half;
Peony roots and ſeeds, in Powder, of each a dram;
red Coral prepar'd, two drams; Vitriol of Steel,
two ſcruples; Salt of Wormwood, two drams;
Juice of Oranges, what ſuffices. Make an Ele-
ctuary, to be taken (to the bigneſs of a Nutmeg)
twice or thrice a day; drinking after it a draught
of the following Julep.
